# Assumptions & Risks

The bets the current plan stands on. An assumption is something you've *accepted as true and built on* —
distinct from an Open question (a gap you know is unresolved). The value is that when a bet breaks — and it's
usually the unwritten one — you can see at a glance what else was riding on it.

For a small project this can be a section in `PROJECT_STATE.md`; for a larger one, its own `docs/risks.md`.

| Assumption / risk | What depends on it | Confidence | If it's wrong → | How to check |
